deck: Founded by Mark and Meridith McGinty, Seventh Avenue Productions is a Minneapolis based small press specializing in trade paperbacks, graphic novels/comic books and anything else that they like and feel a need to publish.
description: Founded by Mark and Meridith McGinty, Seventh Avenue Productions is a Minneapolis based small press specializing in trade paperbacks, graphic novels/comic books and anything else that we like and feel a need to publish. Our first publication was the award winning novel The Cigar Maker. We’ve published historical fiction and also the lighter side of war in the new comic anthology Germ Warfare. In 2011 we published our first non-fiction title, a genealogy book titled Our McGinty Family in America by Gerald K. McGinty Sr. We have two titles slated for 2012, the autobiographical graphic novel Kmart Shoesby Lance Ward and an illustrated children’s book called Lolly Poppet’s Lousy Year. (Source: http://seventh-avenue-productions.com/about/ 05/03/2014)
name: Seventh Avenue Productions

deck: Online, Editorial and Art Gallery Comics, Paintings and Posters (David J Bromley and Phillip Bowles).
description:
The Composition House cartoonists continue their mix of literacy and fun - if you are in Central Virginia, do not miss this two month long exhibition of hard hitting editorial cartoons - with a heavy emphasis on sarcasm, truth and humor!

This show is going to be covered by the Chesterfield Times-Dispatch and The Village News - the same newspaper where David J Bromley and Phillip Bowles got their start as "Locke", their pen-name for all things black and white!

Richmond and Chesterfield Librarians have both recommended Composition House, as well as critics for the Richmond Times-Dispatch, Style Weekly Magazine and Chesterfield Monthly. Come see what everyone is talking about!
name: Composition House
